   Grave's disease causes the thyroid gland to overproduce the
thyroid hormone. Although its specific cause is unknown, the
disease is thought to be related to a reaction of the immune
system. The symptonlarged thyroid gland,
fatigue, heart arrhythmias, insomnia, skin conditions and fatigue.
Some patients also develop swelling in tissues of the eye,
resulting in irritation, pain and light sensitivity.
   The disease can be controlled by a variety of drugs.
